  "mixStrategy": "This sleep-mode rock arrangement strips the genre to its darkest, most enveloping essence \u2014 no drums, extremely sparse, long-sustaining tones that blur into a warm, dark blanket of sound.\n\nFREQUENCY SEPARATION:\n- BASS (Electric Bass, 20-300Hz, MIDI 28-43): Ultra-slow root notes with enormous sustains (8-16s). Provides the gravitational foundation in sub-bass and bass territory. Plays chord roots E1, D2, A1, forming the I\u2192bVII\u2192IV progression in glacial cycles. Velocity 25-40 for a felt-more-than-heard rumble.\n- CHORDS (Warm Pad, 300Hz-2kHz, MIDI 48-67): Sustained power chord voicings (root+5th) that bloom slowly and overlap, creating a continuous harmonic bed. These fill the mid-range warmth zone. Velocity 30-45 for gentle, enveloping warmth. Each chord sustains 8-12s with slow crossfades.\n- MELODY (Overdriven Guitar, 1kHz-8kHz, MIDI 60-76): Extremely sparse pentatonic fragments \u2014 single notes with long sustains (4-8s), like distant guitar harmonics echoing through a vast space. Only 1-2 notes per chord change. Velocity 25-45 for a ghostly, ethereal presence.\n\nHARMONIC COHESION:\nAll three tracks follow the same slow chord progression: Em (I) \u2192 D (bVII) \u2192 Am (IV), cycling approximately every 15 seconds (12 beats at 48 BPM). The progression repeats 3 times across 45 seconds:\n- Cycle 1 (0-15s): Em \u2192 D \u2192 Am \u2014 Energy 0.3, barely audible emergence\n- Cycle 2 (15-30s): Em \u2192 D \u2192 Am \u2014 Energy 0.4-0.5, gentle peak of warmth\n- Cycle 3 (30-45s): Em \u2192 D \u2192 Am \u2014 Energy 0.4\u21920.3, gradual dissolve into silence\n\nRHYTHMIC APPROACH:\nThere is essentially NO rhythm \u2014 just overlapping sustains. Notes enter at slightly staggered times to create a breathing, organic feel. Bass enters first on each chord, pad blooms next, melody floats in last. This staggering creates gentle movement without any pulse. The overall effect is like hearing a rock band from very far away, through walls, as you fall asleep \u2014 just warm harmonic ghosts.",
